# Testing Instructions for Python Applications

## Test Framework

This project uses **pytest** with coverage reporting.

## Running Tests

### Run All Tests

```bash
# From the app/ directory
cd app
make test
```

Or directly with pytest:

```bash
pytest
```

### Run Tests in Docker Container

To run tests inside a Docker container (recommended for consistency):

```bash
# Build the Docker image
cd app
docker build -t python-app-test .

# Run tests in container
docker run --rm python-app-test pytest

# Run tests with coverage in container
docker run --rm python-app-test pytest --cov=app --cov-report=term-missing

# Run tests with verbose output in container
docker run --rm python-app-test pytest -v

# Run specific test file in container
docker run --rm python-app-test pytest tests/test_module.py
```

Note: You may need to modify the `Dockerfile` CMD line temporarily or create a separate `Dockerfile.test` for running tests. To make the Dockerfile work for both running the app and tests, you can override the CMD:

```dockerfile
# Dockerfile optimized for testing
FROM python:3.10

WORKDIR /app

COPY requirements.txt /app/
RUN pip3 install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt

# Install test dependencies
RUN pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest pytest-cov

COPY . /app

# Default command runs the app, but can be overridden
CMD ["python3", "main.py"]
```

### Run Specific Test File

```bash
pytest tests/test_module.py
```

### Run Specific Test Function

```bash
pytest tests/test_module.py::test_function_name
```

### Run with Verbose Output

```bash
pytest -v
```

### Run with Coverage Report

```bash
pytest --cov=app --cov-report=html
```

This generates an HTML coverage report in `htmlcov/index.html`.

### Run with Coverage in Terminal

```bash
pytest --cov=app --cov-report=term-missing
```

